  {
    "client_msg_id": "6a1f1433-cc16-4b88-a31d-ea7a6ee43d39",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I loved the fact that my 8-year-old son was able to jump right in into designing his own game with Pico-8 in the sprite editor. And the sound editor was also easy to learn. So maybe one thing to learn from it is that if a platform offers solid design tools, then that will motivate learning the programming part too? Maybe one of the reasons for success of Flash, HyperCard, Director etc. And the web too — you can start by designing and worry about the code later.\n\nThen again, this creates an artificial barrier between coding and designing, which is not something that I feel to be ideal.",
    "user": "UEQ7QL15F",
    "ts": "1547023870.072900",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
